<section class="pt-faq-hero">
  <div class="pt-faq-hero__content">
    <p class="pt-faq-eye">Got questions</p>
    <h1 class="pt-faq-hero__h1">Everything you need<br><em>to know.</em></h1>
    <p class="pt-faq-hero__sub">If something isn't covered here, drop us a message and we'll get back to you within 24 hours.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="pt-faq-body">
  <div class="pt-faq-inner">

    <!-- FABRIC & QUALITY -->
    <div class="pt-faq-group">
      <p class="pt-faq-group__label">Fabric & Quality</p>

      <div class="pt-faq-item">
        <button class="pt-faq-q" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>What does 240 GSM mean and why does it matter?</span>
          <span class="pt-faq-icon">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="pt-faq-a">
          <p>GSM stands for grams per square metre — it's the standard measure of fabric weight. Most basic t-shirts you'll find in fast fashion are 150–180 GSM. They feel thin, lose shape quickly, and pill after a few washes.</p>
          <p>Our tee is 240 GSM combed ring-spun cotton. The difference is immediate — you feel the density the moment you pick it up. It drapes properly, holds its structure over time, and doesn't go see-through. It's the minimum weight we'd consider acceptable for a tee worth keeping.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="pt-faq-item">
        <button class="pt-faq-q" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>What is combed ring-spun cotton?</span>
          <span class="pt-faq-icon">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="pt-faq-a">
          <p>Combing removes short fibres and impurities from the cotton before spinning. Ring-spinning then twists the remaining long fibres tightly together. The result is a yarn that's finer, stronger, and significantly softer than standard cotton.</p>
          <p>Combined at 240 GSM, you get a fabric that feels substantial but not stiff — soft against the skin with a clean surface that resists pilling.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="pt-faq-item">
        <button class="pt-faq-q" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>Will the tee shrink after washing?</span>
          <span class="pt-faq-icon">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="pt-faq-a">
          <p>No. Our fabric is pre-shrunk before cutting and sewing. What you order is what you'll wear after washing. We've tested this across multiple wash cycles — the measurements stay consistent.</p>
          <p>The only caveat: wash on cold (30°C) and avoid high-heat tumble drying. Heat is the enemy of any cotton garment, pre-shrunk or not.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>

    <!-- FIT & SIZING -->
    <div class="pt-faq-group">
      <p class="pt-faq-group__label">Fit & Sizing</p>

      <div class="pt-faq-item">
        <button class="pt-faq-q" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>How does the fit run? Should I size up or down?</span>
          <span class="pt-faq-icon">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="pt-faq-a">
          <p>The tee is intentionally oversized. If you want the full drop-shoulder drape as designed, go true to size. If you prefer a more controlled oversized look, size down one.</p>
          <p>The best reference is our <a href="/pages/size-guide" class="pt-faq-link">size guide</a> — it has flat garment measurements so you can compare against a tee you already own. That's the most reliable way to get it right.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="pt-faq-item">
        <button class="pt-faq-q" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>What does "drop shoulder" mean and will it suit me?</span>
          <span class="pt-faq-icon">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="pt-faq-a">
          <p>A drop shoulder means the shoulder seam sits below your natural shoulder point — usually partway down your upper arm. It creates a relaxed, wide silhouette that works across body types and is part of what gives the tee its distinctive drape.</p>
          <p>It suits most people well, especially when worn with slim or straight-leg bottoms to balance the volume through the top.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>

    <!-- SHIPPING -->
    <div class="pt-faq-group">
      <p class="pt-faq-group__label">Shipping & Delivery</p>

      <div class="pt-faq-item">
        <button class="pt-faq-q" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>How long does delivery take?</span>
          <span class="pt-faq-icon">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="pt-faq-a">
          <p>Orders are processed within 1–2 business days. Delivery within Delhi NCR typically takes 2–4 business days. For other cities across India, expect 4–7 business days depending on your location.</p>
          <p>You'll receive a tracking link via SMS and email once your order is dispatched.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="pt-faq-item">
        <button class="pt-faq-q" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>Do you offer free shipping?</span>
          <span class="pt-faq-icon">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="pt-faq-a">
          <p>Yes — free shipping on all orders above ₹999. Since our tee is priced at ₹1,499, every order qualifies automatically.</p>
          <p>For orders below ₹999 (if we introduce accessories or other products), a flat shipping fee applies.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="pt-faq-item">
        <button class="pt-faq-q" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>Is Cash on Delivery (COD) available?</span>
          <span class="pt-faq-icon">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="pt-faq-a">
          <p>Yes, COD is available across most pin codes in India. You can select it at checkout. Please note that COD orders may take an additional 1–2 days to process compared to prepaid orders.</p>
          <p>We recommend prepaid orders for faster dispatch and priority processing.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>

    <!-- RETURNS -->
    <div class="pt-faq-group">
      <p class="pt-faq-group__label">Returns & Exchanges</p>

      <div class="pt-faq-item">
        <button class="pt-faq-q" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>What is your return and exchange policy?</span>
          <span class="pt-faq-icon">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="pt-faq-a">
          <p>We offer size exchanges within 7 days of delivery. If the tee doesn't fit as expected, contact us with your order number and we'll arrange an exchange for the correct size — subject to availability.</p>
          <p>The tee must be unworn, unwashed, and in its original condition with tags intact. We don't accept returns for change of mind, but we do take quality issues very seriously.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="pt-faq-item">
        <button class="pt-faq-q" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>What if I receive a damaged or wrong item?</span>
          <span class="pt-faq-icon">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="pt-faq-a">
          <p>That's on us. Email us at <a href="mailto:hello@plaintheory.in" class="pt-faq-link">hello@plaintheory.in</a> with your order number and a photo of the issue within 48 hours of delivery. We'll arrange a replacement or full refund immediately — no questions asked.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>

    <!-- CTA -->
    <div class="pt-faq-cta">
      <h2 class="pt-faq-cta__title">Still have a question?</h2>
      <p class="pt-faq-cta__sub">We reply within 24 hours on all days.</p>
      <div class="pt-faq-cta__btns">
        <a href="mailto:hello@plaintheory.in" class="pt-faq-cta__btn-p">Email us</a>
        <a href="https://wa.me/9936972206" class="pt-faq-cta__btn-s" target="_blank">WhatsApp us</a>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>

<style>
.pt-faq-hero{
  background:#121212;
  min-height:280px;
  display:flex;
  align-items:flex-end;
  padding:60px 48px;
  border-bottom:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.12);
  position:relative;
  overflow:hidden;
}
.pt-faq-hero::before{
  content:'';position:absolute;inset:0;
  background-image:
    repeating-linear-gradient(0deg,transparent,transparent 48px,rgba(255,255,255,0.03) 48px,rgba(255,255,255,0.03) 49px),
    repeating-linear-gradient(90deg,transparent,transparent 48px,rgba(255,255,255,0.03) 48px,rgba(255,255,255,0.03) 49px);
}
.pt-faq-hero__content{position:relative;z-index:1;max-width:620px}
.pt-faq-eye{
  font-size:10px;letter-spacing:0.22em;text-transform:uppercase;
  color:#FFFFFF;margin-bottom:14px;font-family:'DM Sans',sans-serif;
}
.pt-faq-hero__h1{
  font-family:'Playfair Display',serif!important;
  font-size:44px!important;font-weight:400!important;
  color:#FFFFFF!important;line-height:1.1!important;
  margin:0 0 16px!important;
}
.pt-faq-hero__h1 em{font-style:italic;color:#FFFFFF}
.pt-faq-hero__sub{
  font-size:13px;color:#B3B3B3;
  font-weight:300;line-height:1.7;
  font-family:'DM Sans',sans-serif;max-width:480px;
}
.pt-faq-body{background:#121212;padding:64px 48px}
.pt-faq-inner{max-width:760px;margin:0 auto}
.pt-faq-group{margin-bottom:52px}
.pt-faq-group__label{
  font-size:10px;letter-spacing:0.18em;text-transform:uppercase;
  color:#FFFFFF;margin-bottom:20px;font-family:'DM Sans',sans-serif;
  padding-bottom:12px;border-bottom:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.15);
}
.pt-faq-item{
  border-bottom:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08);
}
.pt-faq-q{
  width:100%;display:flex;justify-content:space-between;
  align-items:center;gap:16px;
  padding:20px 0;
  background:transparent;border:none;cursor:pointer;
  text-align:left;
  font-size:14px;color:#FFFFFF;font-weight:400;
  font-family:'DM Sans',sans-serif;
  transition:color 0.2s;
}
.pt-faq-q:hover{color:#FFFFFF}
.pt-faq-q[aria-expanded="true"]{color:#FFFFFF}
.pt-faq-icon{
  flex-shrink:0;
  width:24px;height:24px;
  border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.25);
  border-radius:50%;
  display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;
  font-size:14px;color:#FFFFFF;font-weight:300;
  transition:transform 0.3s,background 0.2s;
  line-height:1;
}
.pt-faq-q[aria-expanded="true"] .pt-faq-icon{
  transform:rotate(45deg);
  background:rgba(255,255,255,0.1);
}
.pt-faq-a{
  max-height:0;overflow:hidden;
  transition:max-height 0.4s ease,padding 0.3s ease;
  padding:0;
}
.pt-faq-a.open{
  max-height:600px;
  padding-bottom:20px;
}
.pt-faq-a p{
  font-size:13px;color:#B3B3B3;line-height:1.85;
  font-family:'DM Sans',sans-serif;font-weight:300;
  margin-bottom:12px;
}
.pt-faq-a p:last-child{margin-bottom:0}
.pt-faq-link{
  color:#FFFFFF;text-decoration:none;
  border-bottom:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.3);
  transition:border-color 0.2s;
}
.pt-faq-link:hover{border-color:#FFFFFF}
.pt-faq-cta{
  text-align:center;
  padding:56px 0 0;
  border-top:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1);
  margin-top:16px;
}
.pt-faq-cta__title{
  font-family:'Playfair Display',serif!important;
  font-size:32px!important;font-weight:400!important;
  color:#FFFFFF!important;margin:0 0 8px!important;
}
.pt-faq-cta__sub{
  font-size:13px;color:#8C8C8C;margin-bottom:28px;
  font-family:'DM Sans',sans-serif;font-weight:300;
}
.pt-faq-cta__btns{display:flex;gap:12px;justify-content:center;flex-wrap:wrap}
.pt-faq-cta__btn-p{
  padding:14px 36px;background:#FFFFFF;color:#121212;
  font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.14em;text-transform:uppercase;
  font-weight:500;border-radius:2px;text-decoration:none;
  font-family:'DM Sans',sans-serif;transition:background 0.2s;
  display:inline-block;
}
.pt-faq-cta__btn-p:hover{background:#FFFFFF}
.pt-faq-cta__btn-s{
  padding:14px 36px;background:transparent;color:#B3B3B3;
  font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.14em;text-transform:uppercase;
  border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.2);border-radius:2px;
  text-decoration:none;font-family:'DM Sans',sans-serif;
  transition:border-color 0.2s,color 0.2s;display:inline-block;
}
.pt-faq-cta__btn-s:hover{border-color:#FFFFFF;color:#FFFFFF}
@media(max-width:768px){
  .pt-faq-hero{padding:40px 24px;min-height:220px}
  .pt-faq-hero__h1{font-size:32px!important}
  .pt-faq-body{padding:48px 24px}
  .pt-faq-q{font-size:13px}
}
</style>

<script>
document.querySelectorAll('.pt-faq-q').forEach(function(btn){
  btn.addEventListener('click',function(){
    var expanded = this.getAttribute('aria-expanded') === 'true';
    var answer = this.nextElementSibling;

    document.querySelectorAll('.pt-faq-q').forEach(function(b){
      b.setAttribute('aria-expanded','false');
      b.nextElementSibling.classList.remove('open');
    });

    if(!expanded){
      this.setAttribute('aria-expanded','true');
      answer.classList.add('open');
    }
  });
});
</script>

